A support group for the presidential aspiration of Asiwaju Bola Tinubu, the Progressives’ Solidarity for Asiwaju (PSA) has appointed a two-term Senator El-Jubril Doguwa, as its Director–General. Unveiling the new PSA DG in Abuja, one of the Conveners of the Progressives’ Solidarity for Asiwaju (PSA), Chief Ibrahim Emokpaire described the new DG as “a great political asset.” Doguwa is an educational planner, an administrator par excellence, an astute politician . He was born in 1955 and hails from Doguwar Giginya town in Doguwa Local Government Area, Kano South Senatorial District of Kano State.   EEFP, Export and Sell prepare exporters to explore $400b…     Abia community deserted following killing of two soldiers     Angry mob set Kogi police barrack ablaze over killing of…   He had held many political appointments before this new appointment. Doguwa was the Executive Chairman of Tundun/Wada Local Government Area of Kano State.  In 1993, he was elected as the State Secretary, National Republican Convention (NRC). He was also the Deputy State Chairman of PDP  in 1999. He was elected a distinguished Senator of the Federal Republic of Nigeria in 1999, representing Kano South Senatorial District between 1999 and 2003.  Between 2006 and 2008, he became the elected Kano State Chairman of PDP. Again, between 2018 and 2019, he was elected Kano State Chairman of PDP. - Advertisement - He was also the Director, Kano State Hotels Management Board. As a distinguished Senator of the Federal Republic of Nigeria, he served in the following committees: Chairman, Senate Committee on Agriculture, Vice Chairman, Senate Committee on Airforce, Vice Chairman, Senate Committee on Information and several appointments in the Senate. He was also a member of various committees of the Kano State Chapter of All Progressives Congress (APC).